    description:
      "Hungarian poet and journalist, widely considered the pivotal figure of Hungarian modernism. Born in \u00c9rmindszent (now \u0102dmuteni, Romania), Ady studied law in Debrecen before becoming a journalist. His first major collection, \u00daj versek (New Poems, 1906), broke decisively with the conventions of 19th-century Hungarian verse and established him as the foremost voice of a new literary generation. Drawing on French Symbolism, Hungarian folk traditions, and the Old Testament, his poetry addresses the themes of love, death, God, and the fate of Hungary with prophetic intensity. He was a leading contributor to the journal Nyugat, which he helped transform into the centre of Hungarian literary modernism.",
