    slug: "lenke-beniczkyne-bajza",
    languageCode: "hu",
    era: "1840\u20131905",
    description:
      "Hungarian novelist and one of the most prolific female writers of the 19th century. Born in Pest as the daughter of the celebrated poet J\u00f3zsef Bajza, she published her first book in 1857. Her marriage to Ferenc Beniczy, who served successively as a county governor, theatre intendant, and under-secretary of the interior, gave her direct access to the aristocratic world she depicted in her fiction. She was elected a member of the Pet\u0151fi Society, becoming one of the first women admitted to Hungarian literary circles. Her novels, typically set among the Hungarian gentry and aristocracy, combine social observation with romantic plots, and she was often compared to the German writer Marlitt.",
