    description:
      "A moral dialogue composed in 1246, addressed to Albertanus's son Johannes, a surgeon. It tells the story of Melibeus, whose house is attacked and daughter wounded, and who must decide whether to seek revenge or follow the counsel of his wife Prudentia. Through Prudentia's speeches, Albertanus weaves together classical, biblical, and legal citations to argue for prudence, deliberation, and reconciliation over violence. The work became one of the most widely translated secular texts of the later Middle Ages: it was rendered into French by Renaud de Louhans (c. 1336), into Italian in the Trecento, and into English by Geoffrey Chaucer as the Tale of Melibee in the Canterbury Tales.",
    descriptionZh:
      "一部道德对话作品，作于1246年，献给阿尔贝塔努斯之子约翰内斯。故事讲述梅利贝乌斯的房屋遭袭、女儿受伤后，他必须在复仇与听从妻子普鲁登蒂亚忠告之间做出抉择。普鲁登蒂亚的论辩交织古典、圣经和法律引文，主张审慎、深思和和解胜于暴力。此书是中世纪晚期流传最广的世俗拉丁文作品之一：约1336年被勒诺·德·卢昂译为法文，后在意大利语中也有译本，杰弗里·乔叟则在《坎特伯雷故事集》中将其英译为《梅利比的故事》。",
