    description:
      "A metafictional novel in which the author himself enters the story as a character, walking the streets of cosmopolitan Istanbul alongside Armenians, Greeks, Levantines, and Turks. Written as an Ottoman experiment in Zola-style naturalism, the novel opens with a literary-critical preface defending realism before unfolding a crime-and-romance narrative across eight books. The author's direct addresses to the reader, interspersed commentary, and self-conscious blurring of fact and fiction make this one of the earliest examples of metafiction in Turkish literature.",
    descriptionZh:
      "一部元小说，作者以角色身份出现在故事中，行走于亚美尼亚人、希腊人、黎凡特人和土耳其人共处的国际化伊斯坦布尔街头。该小说作为奥斯曼帝国对左拉式自然主义的文学实验，以一篇为现实主义辩护的文学批评序言开篇，随后展开横跨八卷的犯罪与爱情交织叙事。作者对读者的直接对话、穿插的评论以及对事实与虚构界限的自觉模糊，使本书成为土耳其文学中最早的元小说范例之一。",
