    languageCode: "ru",
    authorSlug: "pyotr-boborykin",
    description:
      "A three-part novel tracing the rise of Vasily Tyorkin, a peasant-born merchant who builds a fortune through the Volga river trade and Nizhny Novgorod fair. Boborykin uses Tyorkin\u2019s ascent to explore the new commercial energy of post-Emancipation Russia, the tensions between old gentry culture and entrepreneurial ambition, and the moral compromises of self-made wealth. The novel is notable for its detailed rendering of merchant speech, Volga river life, provincial society, and the Makaryev fair world.",
