    languageCode: "la",
    authorSlug: "anonymous-latin",
    description:
      "A collection of moralised exemplary tales compiled in Latin, probably in England or Germany, during the late 13th or early 14th century. Each tale recounts an episode — often attributed to a named Roman emperor — followed by a moral allegory applying the narrative to Christian doctrine. The collection circulated widely in manuscript and print, and furnished source material for later authors including Shakespeare (the pound-of-flesh plot of The Merchant of Venice derives from Tale 195, and the love-test of King Lear from Tale 273). This selection of 25 tales from the full corpus includes stories of faithful daughters, cunning old women, pious saints, and the testing of friendship and conscience.",
    descriptionZh:
      "一部用拉丁语编纂的寓意教化故事集，可能于十三世纪末或十四世纪初在英格兰或德国编成。每则故事讲述一个情节——通常归于某位具名的罗马皇帝——随后附以将叙事应用于基督教教义的道德寓意。该集在手抄本和印刷本中广泛流传，并为后世作家提供了素材，包括莎士比亚（《威尼斯商人》中割肉还债的情节源自第195则，《李尔王》中的爱之考验源自第273则）。本选辑收录全集中的25则故事，包括忠诚的女儿、狡猾的老妇、虔诚的圣徒，以及对友谊和良知的考验。",
    sourceUrl: "https://www.thelatinlibrary.com/gestarom.shtml",
