    description:
      "A Latin hexameter poem in ten distinctiones composed c. 1200 by Alexander Neckam as a verse companion to his prose treatise De Naturis Rerum. The poem covers much of the same encyclopedic ground — the natural world, the elements, animals, and the cosmos — but recast in sustained dactylic hexameter verse with a stronger devotional and contemplative register. Where the prose work mingles natural philosophy with moral allegory, the verse counterpart foregrounds praise of the Creator's wisdom as manifested in creation.",
    descriptionZh:
      "亚历山大·内卡姆约1200年撰写的拉丁语六音步诗，分十个章节，作为其散文论著《论万物之性》的韵文姊妹篇。此诗涵盖了相同的百科全书式领域——自然界、元素、动物与宇宙——但以持续的扬抑扬格六音步韵文重新铸造，带有更强的虔敬与沉思色彩。散文作品将自然哲学与道德寓意交织，韵文则以赞颂造物主在创造中彰显的智慧为核心。",
