      "A Qing dynasty historical novel in three volumes retelling the interwoven careers of the four disciples of the legendary recluse Guiguzi: the military strategists Sun Bin and Pang Juan, and the political rhetoricians Su Qin and Zhang Yi. Set during the Warring States period (475-221 BCE), the novel dramatises the rivalry between Sun Bin and Pang Juan that culminates in the Battle of Maling, Su Qin's promotion of the Vertical Alliance (hezong) against Qin, and Zhang Yi's counter-strategy of the Horizontal Alliance (lianheng) on behalf of the state of Qin. The preface, signed by Yang Danyou of Dongpao and dated to the sixtieth year of Qianlong (1795), positions the work as a corrective to the earlier and cruder Sunpang Yanyi, claiming greater fidelity to the Dong Zhou Lie Guo Zhuan tradition while excising supernatural elements. Each volume is subdivided into two sections, each with a paired couplet title in the classical chapter-novel (zhanghui xiaoshuo) manner.",
