      "A Ming dynasty vernacular fiction in 40 volumes, each volume taking a passage from the Mencius or the Analects as its topic and dramatising the lives of the historical personages mentioned therein. The preface, signed by Leidaoren (磊道人), announces its aim to marry moral instruction with narrative pleasure. The text ranges across the Spring and Autumn and Warring States periods, retelling episodes involving Confucius's disciples (Zilu, Min Ziqian, Zai Yu, Gongye Chang), statesmen and strategists (Guan Zhong, Zichan, Yi Yin, Baili Xi, Sun Shuao), legendary archers and musicians (Yi, Feng Meng, Music Master Kuang), and philosophers (Mozi, Yangzi, Chunyu Kun). Each volume opens with a poem, proceeds through a narrative interspersed with verse, and closes with a critical commentary (zongping). The chapter titles quote the classical source directly, creating a bridge between the Confucian canon and popular storytelling.",
    descriptionZh:
      "明代白话小说，共四十卷，每卷以《孟子》或《论语》中的一句话为题，将其中提及的历史人物故事演绎为通俗叙事。序言署名磊道人，表明其将义理与趣味结合的写作宗旨。全书内容涵盖春秋战国时期，重述了孔子弟子（子路、闵子骞、宰予、公冶长）、政治家与谋略家（管仲、子产、伊尹、百里奠、孙叔敖）、传奇弓箭手与音乐家（羿、逢蒙、师旷）以及哲学家（墨子、杨子、淳于髡）的故事。每卷以诗开篇，穿插韵文于叙事之中，末尾附有总评。卷题直接引用经典原文，架起了儒家典籍与通俗讲史之间的桥梁。",
    sourceUrl: "https://zh.wikisource.org/wiki/七十二朝人物演義",
