      "The companion text to the Zhongdou Dakui Baoming Jing, this scripture focuses specifically on the exorcistic and demon-subduing aspects of the Central Dipper's Great Overseer. Where the companion text describes protective ritual protocol, this text frames the Central Dipper's power through a sustained incantatory formula: the Dao's formless nature is paired with the Great Overseer's ability to dominate demonic forces through the power of spiritual calculation (掌算). Practitioners who recite this scripture ten thousand times are promised that demons and evil spirits will flee, weapons will not harm them, and they will eventually ascend to the celestial realm. The text is notably compact, presenting its teaching as a single sustained incantation rather than a dialogue, reflecting the distinctive genre of divine spell scriptures (神呪經) within the Daoist canon.",
