    description:
      "An unusually substantial Northern Dipper text structured as twenty-eight chapters, framed as a revelation to the Han dynasty Emperor Ming during an encounter at Zhongnan Mountain with a woman who reveals herself as a celestial envoy of the Jade Emperor and a spirit of the Northern Dipper. Each chapter teaches a specific meditational, ritual, or ethical practice associated with the Dipper's seven-plus-two stars, covering topics such as mental stillness, dream cultivation, avoiding false speech, reverence for parents, and the circulation of life-force qi. The text represents an integration of Northern Dipper stellar religion with broader Daoist self-cultivation traditions, including elements common to both the Lingbao and Shangqing traditions. Its twenty-eight chapter structure may echo the twenty-eight lunar lodges (二十八宿) that the Dipper traverses in its annual rotation.",
