    slug: "sanguo-yanyi",
    languageCode: "zh",
    authorSlug: "luo-guanzhong",
    description:
      "One of the Four Great Classical Novels of Chinese literature, attributed to Luo Guanzhong. The novel dramatises the turbulent century from the decline of the Eastern Han dynasty through the Three Kingdoms period (c. 169–280 CE), weaving together historical events, military strategy, and character studies of figures such as Liu Bei, Cao Cao, and Zhuge Liang. Drawing on Chen Shou’s third-century Records of the Three Kingdoms and Pei Songzhi’s annotations, the narrative balances fidelity to historical sources with fictional elaboration, particularly in its portrayal of alliances, betrayals, and the interplay of loyalty and ambition. The 120-chapter edition, the most widely circulated version, was revised and annotated by Mao Zonggang and his father Mao Lun in the Qing dynasty.",
