    titleZh: "\u65b0\u8bd7\u96c6",
    authorSlug: "endre-ady",
    description:
      "Endre Ady's debut collection of 1906, which inaugurated Hungarian modernist poetry. Organised in four thematic cycles \u2014 the Psalms of Lady L\u00e9da, On the Hungarian Fallow, The Singing Paris, and Wanderer of Virgin Peaks \u2014 the collection draws on French Symbolism, Hungarian folk imagery, and personal experience. The poems express erotic longing, national anguish, and a prophetic sense of cultural transformation. Ady had spent time in Paris, and the collection reflects both his encounter with French modernism and his troubled relationship with the poet\u00e9ss Adda Gy\u00f6r\u00f6s\u00e9y (Lady L\u00e9da). The book was a cultural shock to Hungarian readers and launched a bitter literary controversy.",
