    titleZh: "\u8c01\u770b\u89c1\u8fc7\u6211",
    authorSlug: "endre-ady",
    description:
      "A poetry collection of 1914, published as war was breaking out across Europe. Organised in five cycles, the poems respond to the impending catastrophe with a prophetic voice shaped by personal and national anxiety. The cycle 'Bloody Panoramas in Spring' directly engages the coming war; 'The Tree of Necessity' and 'The Pipe of Old Superstition' address death and Hungarian fate; 'The Lost Families' mourns broken communal bonds; 'Autumn Red Flowers' turns to love and mortality. The collection was Ady's last major work before his health began to fail.",
