    languageCode: "en",
    authorSlug: "william-makepeace-thackeray",
    description:
      "A sequel to The History of Henry Esmond, following Henry Esmond's twin grandsons George and Harry Warrington through the American colonies and England during the mid-eighteenth century. George is captured during Braddock's expedition in the French and Indian War and presumed dead; Harry crosses to London, where he falls into debt and bad company among the fashionable circles of Georgian society. The novel spans the 1750s to the American Revolution, with the brothers finding themselves on opposite sides of the conflict — George a Loyalist officer, Harry a Continental general.",
    descriptionZh:
      "《亨利·埃斯蒙德的历史》的续篇，追随亨利·埃斯蒙德的孪生孙子乔治和哈里·沃灵顿在十八世纪中叶穿梭于美洲殖民地与英格兰之间的经历。小说跨越十七世纪五十年代至美国独立战争，兄弟二人最终站在了冲突的对立面。",
