    authorSlug: "isabella-harwood",
    description:
      "A Victorian sensation novel set in the English countryside. Florence Cleve, an orphaned young woman of reduced means, arrives at Abbot's Cleve to stay with her wealthy cousin Augusta and her Italian husband, Count Almonti. What begins as an uncomfortable visit to a household of social condescension deepens into a mystery of suspicious illness, a night-time intruder, and a question of poison. The novel balances domestic social comedy \u2014 Augusta's brittle vanity, the manoeuvring of county families \u2014 against an escalating Gothic plot as Florence is drawn into possession of a dangerous secret she cannot safely share.",
