    titleZh: "\u5361\u5C14\u987F\u5E84\u56ED",
    slug: "carleton-grange",
    languageCode: "en",
    authorSlug: "isabella-harwood",
    description:
      "A Victorian sensation novel centred on Maud Fleming, the young mistress of Carleton Grange, whose comfortable world is shattered when Francis Godfrey, a menacing family guest, reveals that she may not be the legitimate heir to the estate she calls home. The novel unfolds across a tightly plotted second volume as Godfrey's blackmail, Maud's secret love for Philip Ormond of Ormond Hall, and a web of forged documents converge on questions of identity, inheritance, and the vulnerability of women without legal protection. Harwood's narrative combines the Gothic machinery of the sensation genre with a domestic precision that recalls Wilkie Collins.",
