    languageCode: "en",
    authorSlug: "charlotte-m-yonge",
    description:
      "Published in 1895, this novel follows the Carbonel family as they take up residence in a neglected rural parish and work to improve the condition of its inhabitants. Captain Edmund Carbonel and his sisters Mary and Sophia confront rural poverty, ignorance, and entrenched resistance to change, establishing schools, mothers' meetings, and church life over the course of several decades. The story traces the slow transformation of the village of Uphill Priors from a place of squalor and indifference into a functioning community, illustrating Yonge's conviction that patient, personal engagement achieves what legislation and grand schemes cannot.",
