    description:
      "A historical novel set during the Young Turk Revolution of 1908, the constitutional uprising that curtailed the autocratic rule of Sultan Abdulhamid II. The story follows Shirin, a young Turkish woman in Salonika, and Ramiz, a journalist and member of the Committee of Union and Progress, whose love is imperilled by the spy Sa'ib and the sultan's repressive apparatus. Through their personal drama, Zaidan dramatises the clandestine organisation of the revolutionary movement, the atmosphere of suspicion and espionage in the late Ottoman Empire, and the events leading to the restoration of the constitution. The novel blends fictional romance with historical figures such as Niyazi Bey and Enver Pasha, offering a vivid account of the revolutionary fervour that swept Macedonia and Constantinople in the final years of Hamidian rule. An appended historical essay surveys the constitutional movement from the deposition of Sultan Abdulaziz through the Young Turk uprising.",
    descriptionZh:
      "一部以1908年青年土耳其革命为背景的历史小说，描绘了限制苏丹阿卜杜勒·哈米德二世专制统治的立宪运动。故事围绕萨洛尼卡的年轻土耳其女子希琳和统一与进步委员会成员、记者拉米兹展开，他们的爱情受到间谍萨伊卜和苏丹镇压机器的威胁。宰丹通过他们的个人命运，生动再现了革命运动的秘密组织、晚期奥斯曼帝国的猜疑与间谍氛围，以及恢复宪政的历史进程。小说将虚构的爱情故事与尼亚齐贝伊、恩维尔帕夏等历史人物融为一体，展现了哈米德统治末年席卷马其顿和君士坦丁堡的革命热潮。书末附有历史论文，概述了从苏丹阿卜杜勒·阿齐兹被废到青年土耳其起义的宪政运动。",
